</taxonomicName>
zur Strassen, 1975, p. 260
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1155,794,958]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">
Previously known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[515,560,794,819]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">Iran</collectingCountry>
, this species is here recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[960,1105,794,819]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="zur Strassen" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[335,491,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taghizadehi">
<emphasis box="[335,491,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">E. taghizadehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(zur Strassen) from which it can be distinguished by the straight paired processes on tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[642,754,864,889]" captionStart="Figures 22–31" captionStartId="7.[160,235,1558,1581]" captionTargetBox="[164,1150,146,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[163,1153,142,1527]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 22–31. Eremiothrips species. Male tergite IX: (22) E. aldryhimi sp. nov., (23) E. arya (zur Strassen), (24) E. efflatouni (Priesner), (25) E. similis Bhatti, (26) E. unicolour sp. nov. Male sternites III–VII: (27) E. aldryhimi sp. nov., (28) E. arya (zur Strassen), (29) E. efflatouni (Priesner), (30) E. similis Bhatti, (31) E. unicolour sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5529894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5529894/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">Figure 23</figureCitation>
) (in contrast to paired processes recurved at apex) and the wider pore plates on sternites IV–VII (
<figureCitation box="[901,1009,898,923]" captionStart="Figures 22–31" captionStartId="7.[160,235,1558,1581]" captionTargetBox="[164,1150,146,1524]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[163,1153,142,1527]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 22–31. Eremiothrips species. Male tergite IX: (22) E. aldryhimi sp. nov., (23) E. arya (zur Strassen), (24) E. efflatouni (Priesner), (25) E. similis Bhatti, (26) E. unicolour sp. nov. Male sternites III–VII: (27) E. aldryhimi sp. nov., (28) E. arya (zur Strassen), (29) E. efflatouni (Priesner), (30) E. similis Bhatti, (31) E. unicolour sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5529894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5529894/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610">Figure 28</figureCitation>
) (in contrast to less wide pore plates) (
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei K" box="[448,587,933,958]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1610" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref7772" refString="Minaei K. 2012. The genus Eremiothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran, with one new species. Zootaxa. 3349 (1): 56 - 62. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3349.1.6" type="journal article" year="2012">Minaei 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
